Head lenticular, slightly narrower (
0.26–0.27 mm
) than pronotum (
Figure 2
). Frontal sulci divergent. Microsculpture of cephalic disc polygonal, mostly isodiametric except in a small central area where microsculpture is lessened (no striated surface is observed). Antennae moniliform (
Figure 2
), with noticeably setulated antennomeres. Labrum rectangular. Mandibles sharpened. Labium transverse, with a notch that is armed with a conspicuous tooth (blunt) that does not exceed the anterior end of the epilobe (
Figure 3A
). Prebasilar is separated from labium by a transverse suture (
Figure 3B
). Labial and maxillary palps have typical shape and chaetotaxy of genus.

Pronotum trapezoidal (
Figure 2
), longer (
0.34–0.35 mm
) than wide (
0.32–0.33 mm
). Proximal margin nearly as wide as distal margin. Posterior angles indicated by a small tooth preceded by marginal edge, which is slightly wavy (
Figure 3B
). The microsculpture is polygonal and isodiametric.

Elytral chaetotaxy (
Figure 2
): numerous setae on disc, although some are somewhat longer than others, such as scutellar pore seta, and three or four discal setae, longitudinally aligned parallel to longitudinal carina. Setae of umbilicate series, whose formula is (4+3), stand out because of their large size.

Abdomen with two long setae in males and four in females in last sternite,. Apodemal ring elliptical (
Figure 4E
). Median lobe of aedeagus (
Figure 4A,B
) is 174 µm in length. It is slightly curved and the apex points downward slightly compared with basal lamina. Internal sac is small and resembles the Greek letter ‘gamma’. Parameres with two setae, left one with a normal, subtriangular appearance, and right one narrow, abnormally long and hyaline (
Figure 4C,D
).

This new species is named after Dr Josabel Belliure from the Department of Ecology at Alcalá University (
Spain
), who worked on the first exploration of the endogean environment of the Ponoig mountain range.
